==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symphyla
<hw>Sym*phy"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ a clan.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order of small apterous insects having an elongated body, with three
pairs of thoracic and about nine pairs of abdominal legs. They are, in
many respects, intermediate between myriapods and true
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

